The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:18 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.3 percent to 4,229.26.  Cap SA (CAP)   gained 0.6 percent to 19,308 pesos.  Chile â€™s
largest steel producer and iron miner will double planned
capacity at a water desalination project in northern Chile,
according to a filing sent to regulators yesterday.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC CC) rose 1.7 percent to 6.901 pesos,
its highest price in three weeks. Trading volume today was more
than five times the three-month average after the Chilean lender
had its weighting increased in the MSCI Latin America and MSCI
Chile indexes.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 3.1 percent to
477.27 pesos, its second day of losses. The Chilean department
store operator hired Lazard Ltd. and MBA Lazard to advise on its
financial restructuring process. The company also increased by
511,000 the number of clients that had suffered unilateral
consumer loan restructurings.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   rose a record 12.2 percent to 870
pesos. The Chilean holding company confirmed its in negotiations
to sell its home appliances unit CTI Cia. Tecno Industrial SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
